Samsung recently unveiled its Galaxy S10 smartphones at its Unpacked 2019 event. The company announced that its Galaxy S10e, Galaxy S10, and Galaxy S10+ smartphones would be available to pre-order from today – and will launch in South Africa on 8 March 2019. The devices will be available in three colours: Prism White, Prism Black, and Prism Green. The Galaxy S10e will be available in Canary Yellow, it added. The recommended retail pricing for the new devices is as follows: Samsung’s Galaxy S10 smartphones are currently available for pre-order from Vodacom, MTN, Telkom, and Cell C, with contract packages available alongside cash purchases. All South Africans who pre-order any Samsung Galaxy S10 device, including the Galaxy S10e, will also receive a free pair of Galaxy Buds, said the company. We compared some of the best contract prices for the Samsung Galaxy S10e, S10, and S10+ below, based on deals available at the time of writing.   